3... Bf5 4. Bb2 e6 5. Nh4
{ This is another rather fresh and creative idea that Nakamura used on several occasions in 2019-2021. We are immediately going after opponent's bishop pair. }
5... Bg4 6. Be2 Bxe2 7. Qxe2
{ The knight on h4 looks a bit weird now, but White has ideas related to f2-f4 and Nf3-e5, and our dark-squared bishop is incredibly powerful here. }
7... Be7
{ Here the moves ....Be7, ....c5 and....O-O are very transposable and tend to lead to the same position regardless of the order played. So, please focus on the ideas, not specific move order details. }
8. O-O O-O 9. f4 { Looks like a very good plan to me as well, for example }
9... c5 10. Nf3 Nc6 11. d3 Qd7 12. Nbd2
{ White is about to continue with Ne5, g2-g4-g5, Qh5, Rf3-h3, etc, with some very typical attacking ideas on the kingside. }
