{ This is another typical move that was tried by several strong players; Black intends to reinforce the knight with ...f7-f5. I believe that in these positions, ...f7-f5 is an excellent plan for Black if the pawn is on  c7  , because the center is stable; however, ...c7-c5 makes it a bit unreliable, and we still have our typical queenside plan with Ba6, whichwe saw after  10...Rc8  11.cxd5  . }
