{ We are preparing to take on c5 and meet the recapture with a piece with b3-b4, grabbing space @@StartBracket@@of course, if ...Nxc5, we need to make we don't hang our darling of a light-squared bishop!@@EndBracket@@. }
12... cxd4
{ Black releases the tension, taking advantage of the fact the White bishop cannot ever take on d4, as the a3-pawn would hang. }
13. Nxd4
{ The White bishop is more active on b3 than the Black one is on e7.  The dream here is to put pressure on the diagonals, potentially with Qa1 in the future, or with Nc6, using the weak c6-square. If it was our turn, b3-b4 would be rather promising, grabbing space. }
13... Rxc1 14. Qxc1
{ Let's see how the only top-level game that reached this position continued. }
14... Ne5 15. Be2 Qa8 16. Nxe6
{ Okay, this was a blitz game, so you can certainly be critical and say Black didn't need to lose this way. But, it does show that the tempting ...Ne5 jump can be rather dangerous for him!: 1-0  @@StartBracket@@32@@EndBracket@@ Nakamura,H @@StartBracket@@2736@@EndBracket@@-Tabatabaei,M @@StartBracket@@2629@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2021 }
