1. Nf3 d5 2. e3 Nf6 3. b3 Bg4
{ This is the move suggested by GM Mikhalevski in his book Grandmaster Repertoire - Beating Minor Openings. The key difference between this and the Slav setup with ...c7-c6 and ...Bg4 is that Black chooses to not commit to ...c7-c6 yet, which leaves the options of ...c7-c5, or of ...Nd7 and quick ...e7-e5 open.   Additionally, it is proposed by GM Kornev in his book Practical Black repertoire with d5, c6. So, we can kill two birds with one shot if we find a way to pose problems here! Spoiler: we will find a way :@@EndBracket@@ }
