{ I believe it is rather vital to immediately make Black decide whether he wants to give up the bishop pair in the hopes of getting a slightly inferior but solid position, or whether he is comfortable about the idea of keeping the tension. }
4... Bh5 5. Bb2 e6 6. g4
{ We immediately make sure we get the bishop pair while following in the footsteps of Nakamura, Grischuk, Edouard and many other strong GMs. }
6... Bg6 7. Nh4 Be4
{ Does not look very promising to me as now we either have to retreat with the knight @@StartBracket@@which is pointless@@EndBracket@@, or play Rg1. }
8. Rg1
{ But this is just the tempo Black needs to give the bishop a retreating sqaure. }
8... h6
{ And Black's bishop is safe, while White's development is really weird. } *

