7. d4 b6 8. c4
{ It is not good to develop the bishop to b7 when it can get quickly shut down with d4-d5!, and, of course, this rule is the case here as well. By the way, a similar scenario is covered in one of the model games in the chapter on the Double Fianchetto. }
8... Bb7 9. Nc3 Nbd7
{ And, surprisingly, we got to a position covered in the chapter on KID, too! }
