{ The most popular decision by far: Black is not showing his hand yet, choosing to wait and possibly follow up with ...e7-e5 shortly after, or with ...c7-c5, or with something slow like ...c7-c6, ...Qc7, etc. }
7. O-O Re8
{ Is another interesting waiting move.  In this case, we'll show the opponent that we've learned a lot from neural networks, which always push the a or h-pawns whenever given the chance in order to grab as much space as possible. }
8. a4
{ The arising positions will be either similar to the ones in the main line if Black plays ...e7-e5 and meets dxe5 with ...Ng4, as the pawn structure is going to be identical, or to the ones discussed after 6...c7-c6 and ...Qc7, if Black continues slow play. }
