{ The most popular decision by far: Black is not showing his hand yet, choosing to wait and possibly follow up with ...e7-e5 shortly after, or with ...c7-c5, or with something slow like ...c7-c6, ...Qc7, etc. }
7. O-O e5
{ Usually, the Black players choose to immediately challenge us in the center. }
8. dxe5 Ng4 9. c4 dxe5
{ This is a more principled way for Black to proceed, as he is not weakening his pawn structure. But, it is not a great idea for tactical reasons. }
10. h3 Nh6 11. Qc2
