[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Anti-Grunfeld "]
[Black "6....b6 #1 - piece activity"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 Nf6 2. b3 g6 3. Bb2 Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. d4 d5
{ In the Grunfeld style, Black also grabs a fair share of the center, fighting for the c4 and e4-squares.   White can choose to either develop slowly, or to challenge the center right away with c2-c4. That move is not bad, but if Black knows what he is doing, he will be able to get a relatively safe position pretty fast. However, I still recommend that we play the principled move 6.c4, because as practice shows, Black players are not aware of the right path! }
6. c4
{ Now, Black will either counterattack in the center with ...c7-c5, or play ...c7-c6, reinforcing it. Some people also tried ...b7-b6 and ...e7-e6, which are not terrible continuations, so we'll look at those as well. }
6... b6 { Is very likely to transpose to the lines after 6...e6. } 7. Nbd2 Bb7
8. Be2 Nbd7 9. Rc1
{ Now, ...e7-e6 will be a direct transposition. Instead, Black can choose to counterattack the center right away. }
9... c5
{ This is a very smart choice, which will bring him close to equality. } 10.
O-O
{ It does not make sense to hurry and capture Black's central pawns.  Why so? Well, because if he takes himself, it will only help activate our minor pieces! }
10... cxd4 11. Bxd4 { Activates our bishop. } 11... dxc4 12. Nxc4
{ Now, I would not go as far as to claim Black is in trouble here, but I am certainly struggling to see why he would want to activate our pieces. Next, we should proceed with Qd2-b2!, securing a much better control over the long diagonal in the typical Queen's Indian style, followed by Rfd1. }
12... Rc8 13. Qd2 Nc5 14. Qb2
{ We have such ideas as Rfd1, Nce5, maybe b3-b4 to kick the Black knight away and gain space, or even b4-b5 to secure the c6-square as an outpost. While this is certainly not the end of the world for Black, he is clearly a lot less active and has to deal with a number of small annoying threats and nuisances, which means the opening was a success for us. }
