[White "Anti-Dutch"]
[Black "2...d5 3.Bg5 h6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

{ Welcome to the chapter on the Anti-Dutch! I've spent a long time thinking about what to recommend against this opening, and that is primarily not because it's hard to fight for the advantage, but because we don't want to engage in highly theoretical opening discussions, and even more importantly, we do not want to be move-ordered into some variation that does not fit with the rest of this repertoire. Therefore, I hope you forgive me for not sticking to the pure b2-b3 plans which are typical of the rest of the course! However, I am really excited to show you the sideline that I find very promising, yet really easy to learn and relatively little-known. }
1. Nf3 f5 2. d4
{ Okay, we seem to be going for the main setups with d4! But, we won't enter the mainline theory, don't worry. Now, most people who play the Dutch would stay flexible with ... Nf6, but it's certainly also worth checking out such moves as 2...g6, 2...e6 and 2...d5. }
2... d5 { Is certainly possible, but doesn't solve the problems. } 3. Bg5 h6 4.
Bf4 Nf6 5. e3
{ Seems to be a very good version of the QGD with a weird pawn on f5. Or, if you will, a typical Stonewall, which went really wrong for Black. Why is that? Well, normally the Stonewall works best versus the g2-g3 setups, but this time, our typically inactive dark-squared bishop managed to rapidly get outside the pawn chain. Addtionally, Black heavily weakened his position with ...h7-h6, which is a huge deal, because Ne5 will now always threaten ideas like Ng6.  It's never a great sign to have a weak g6-square this early! }
5... e6 6. c4 Bd6 7. Nc3 O-O 8. Rc1
{ We are hoping Black would go ...c7-c6, which will enable us to take on d6 without allowing for ...cxd6. }
8... c6 9. Bxd6 Qxd6 10. Bd3
{ White just has a very comfortable version of the Stonewall, as Black ended up with all weak dark squares and no counterplay; unlike in the main Stonewall positions with g2-g3, our bishop is not blocked on the long diagonal, but is instead an active and promising piece. }
